# Netscape HTTP Cookie File
# This is the standard format yt-dlp accepts via --cookies / cookiefile.
# Export from a logged-in browser (Chrome/Firefox) using an extension like
# "Get cookies.txt LOCALLY" and save the result here as cookies.txt:
#
#   ./secrets/cookies.txt
#
# Then set in .env:
#   YT_DLP_COOKIES_PATH=/run/cookies.txt
#
# Lines below are an example structure; replace with your real cookies.
# Real cookies.txt is gitignored.
#
# .youtube.com  TRUE  /  TRUE  1234567890  CONSENT  YES+...
